          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for private or public consultation and recitation during observances performed on the ninth day in the bright half of the month of Bhaudra (August/September) in honor of the Great Goddess (Mahādevī), whom women worship to avert evil in the coming year. Presented as a discourse between the legendary author Vyāsa and the sages (ṛṣis).</summary>
